<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-09T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="810" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1261: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul General at Beirut</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-09T19:00:00-05:00">November 9, 1938—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your telegram of November 8, 3 p.m. If you have not already done so,
                                it is suggested that you acknowledge the communications addressed to
                                you concerning Palestine and furnish such correspondents with the
                                Department’s public statement on the subject contained in radio
                                bulletin No. 241 of October 14, 1938. You may add that the statement
                                represents no change in this Government’s position in the
                                matter.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>